<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>HealthThread Pilot Brief</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: #111827; line-height: 1.5; margin: 40px; }
    h1 { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
    h2 { font-size: 16px; margin-top: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid #d1d5db; padding-bottom: 4px; }
    p, li { font-size: 12px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>HealthThread - Pilot Brief</h1>
  <p><strong>Category:</strong> Healthcare AI<br><strong>Stage:</strong> Pre-Seed<br><strong>Source:</strong> Hospital pilot memo</p>

  <h2>What It Does</h2>
  <p>HealthThread integrates with hospital EMR systems and surfaces relevant case history, drug interaction warnings, and clinical guidelines while emergency physicians write notes.</p>

  <h2>Team</h2>
  <p><strong>Dr. Ananya Sharma:</strong> ER physician with 10 years of experience at AIIMS Delhi.</p>
  <p><strong>Karan Mehta:</strong> Ex-Google Health engineer who built ML infrastructure for medical imaging products.</p>

  <h2>Traction</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Six-month pilot live at Fortis Mumbai.</li>
    <li>200 patients processed through the workflow.</li>
    <li>EMR integration is live without requiring a new physician workflow.</li>
    <li>Hospital legal team approved data handling under DPDP requirements.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Open Questions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>When will clinical outcome data be available?</li>
    <li>Who is conducting the third-party security audit?</li>
    <li>What does expansion to the next two hospitals look like?</li>
  </ul>
</body>
</html>
